snippet.textDisplay: I worked for the state for 5 years where I was harassed, assaulted and received death threats from coworkers.  When I was assaulted (no worries, I'm fine), all I did was report the incident and the chief goes, "Do you feel threatened?"  No pause.  "Because if your telling me you feel threatened, I have to report this to the ethics commission and I don't want to do that so I'm just going to fire you"  Just breezing right past the threats I did receive, past the assault that did occur and all the rest of the horribleness I experienced.  I talked to my union rep and her only response was to sneer at me and say, "sometimes people get discriminated against".  True story.  No attorney would help me, they would say they would get back to me, I presuming after a phonecall, and then tell me sorry, what happened is horrible and they can't help.  2 of which told me because I'm white.  My story should be on the 8 o'clock news.  The rule of law is not in control in new jersey.  Clearly some people are above the law.  New Jersey is ruled by the power of whoever is in charge.  It is an evil, corrupt, lawless government.  NJ state government is illegitimate.  What law matters after that?  My story should be on the 8 oclock news.
